{{Quote|Pomojema, god of the Kaiburr. It almost seems familiar, somehow. That's crazy, of course.|Halla|<ref name="SotME" />}}
'''Pomojema''' was a minor [[God/Legends|god]] who was worshiped by natives of [[Mimban/Legends|Mimban]] as a healer-god, before the planet's mining settlements grew culturally disruptive. He was believed to have a [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] body, wings, and a face of tentacles. Priests of the [[Temple of Pomojema]] used a [[Kaiburr crystal]] to amplify their [[Force power/Legends|Force powers]].

==History==
{{Quote|Nobody wants his neighbor's god to have a bigger reputation than his own. But with this Pomojema, those legends could hold some truth.|Halla|<ref name="SotME" />}}
The [[Mimbanite]]s, [[Coway]]s, [[Thrella]], and other sentients of the planet [[Mimban/Legends|Mimban]] had thousands of deities, each of which had their own temples and sanctuaries scattered across the planet. Of these Pomojema hardly stood out. A minor god of healing, the exact nature of Pomojema's worship and powers had been all but lost to history by the time of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] occupation during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Those who did know about Pomojema often thought the tales of miraculous healing done in his service were little more than superstitions. However, the [[Temple of Pomojema]] was the resting place of the fabulous [[Kaiburr crystal]], an artifact that amplified the [[Force power/Legends|Force power]] of anyone who used it. It was possible that the tales of Pomojema's healing abilities were a result of [[Force healing/Legends|Force healing]] amplified through use of the Kaiburr crystal.<ref name="SotME" />

By the year [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]] the Temple of Pomojema had been abandoned, save for a [[Hssiss]] who had taken up residence there, possibly due to the Kaiburr crystal's connection with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] dueled [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], who sought the Kaiburr crystal in the temple, giving their associate [[Halla]] the chance to claim the crystal.<ref name="SotME" />

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|This Pomojema was a minor god, but one who was supposed to be able to give his priests the ability to perform miraculous feats.|Halla|<ref name="SotME" />}}
Pomojema was known for his healing ability. The statue of Pomojema in his temple depicted him as vaguely humanoid, with two leathery wings, and hands and feet with enormous claws. Beneath his eyes there was no humanoid face, but rather a collection of writhing tentacles.<ref name="SotME" />

==Behind the scenes==
Author [[Joseph Bongiorno]] has hinted at a connection between Pomojema and [[Typhojem/Legends|Typhojem]]. While the connection has not been made explicit in any published source, comments by Bongiorno give credence to the description of Pomojema's image being quite similar to the description of the god-creature [[Wikipedia:Cthulhu|Cthulhu]] described in the works of horror writer [[Wikipedia:H. P. Lovecraft|Howard Phillips Lovecraft]].<ref name="endnotes">{{Blogspot|subdomain=geekosity|url=2012/03/endnotes-for-star-wars-book-of-sith.html|name=Daniel Wallace's Geekosity|text=Endnotes for Star Wars: Book of Sith (part 1)}}</ref>

Early concept art for ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'' used the Temple of Pomojema as a setting, before the [[Temple of the Kyber]] was developed to replace it.<ref name="ArtR1">''[[The Art of Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref>

